  "prompt": "Is there anyone from Heritage Institute of Technology ,Kolkata; who have pursued or planning to pursue PG in Physics after their Btech?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible that some students from the Heritage Institute of Technology (HIT) in Kolkata may pursue or plan to pursue a postgraduate (PG) degree in Physics after completing their BTech. While HIT is primarily known for its engineering programs, it does offer a BTech in Electronics and Communication Engineering, which can sometimes lead students to develop an interest in Physics or related fields.\n\nStudents who have a strong interest in Physics or theoretical concepts may choose to pursue further studies in the subject, either in India or abroad. However, this is not a common path for BTech graduates, who typically continue in engineering or related fields.\n\nIf you are specifically looking for individuals who have taken this path, you might want to connect with alumni networks, social media groups, or forums related to HIT or Physics education. Platforms like LinkedIn or the institute's alumni association could be useful for finding such individuals. Additionally, you can reach out to the academic advisors or faculty at HIT for guidance or information on past students who have pursued Physics after their BTech.",
